      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 26: `resolveBubbleBody` always computes `fallback` by stripping markdown before trying the existing inline-link attributed text. For plain text messages with bare URLs and no markdown, this is harmless, but for malformed/partial markdown plus a URL it can silently alter the visible fallback even though no markdown was actually rendered. Keep fallback equal to the original content unless `isRenderable` is true, or pass the original content as the fallback for the inline-link-only path.\n```suggestion\n        let fallback \u003d isRenderable ? MessageMarkdownPlainText.display(from: content, isRenderable: true) : content\n```",
