      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Major] Line 41: When a message contains block syntax, the bubble is rendered as plain stripped text and `inlineLinkAttributed` is ignored. This regresses existing inline URL tapping for messages such as `\u003e see https://example.com` or list items containing a URL, because the previous inline link renderer would still make the URL tappable. Preserve the inline-link fallback when markdown cannot be rendered richly.\n```suggestion\n        if #available(iOS 15.0, *), !hasBlockSyntax {\n            if let markdown \u003d attributedString(\n                from: content,\n                linkColor: linkColor,\n                baseFont: baseFont,\n                isRenderable: isRenderable\n            ) {\n                return .rich(markdown, fallbackPlain: fallback)\n            }\n        }\n        if #available(iOS 15.0, *), let inlineLinkAttributed \u003d inlineLinkAttributed as? AttributedString {\n            return .rich(inlineLinkAttributed, fallbackPlain: fallback)\n        }\n```",
      "revId": "2103822cdd04c4e2830ad0fe33175b0af7c74665",
      "serverId": "1e26b4c1-6b8c-47ff-9df7-501b633d3b5a"
