      "side": 1,
      "message": "[Critical] Line 74: Markdown parsing accepts every link destination that Foundation turns into a link attribute. That lets remote message text create tappable links with non-web schemes, which is a behavior expansion from the existing bare-URL handling that only accepts http/https/www. Filter parsed markdown links to allowed schemes before returning the AttributedString.\n```suggestion\n        sanitizeLinks(in: \u0026result, linkColor: linkColor)\n```\nFor example, remove `run.link` unless `scheme` is `http` or `https`, then only style the remaining links.",
      "revId": "2103822cdd04c4e2830ad0fe33175b0af7c74665",
